<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100291666229928></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100291666229928><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=10704&mid=100291666229928>DAY ONE Hunting and Gathering</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=10704&mid=100291666229928#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=10704><span id=Scholar>The One and Only JanaLaser</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>22 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 12th 3:57 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I headed down the ramp. My hands were icy, but I was ready. The river took a few minutes to get to. I then followed it until I found the road. There were resplendently dressed guardians on the road, and all around them there were people hunting what looked to be rather small creatures of various types. <br><br>I was fascinated for several minutes by spells being fired in all directions. So beautiful to look at, and then I recalled my abilities, rather sheepishly, and tried my hand at casting a protective shield over myself, just in case a wandering animal decided it liked my scent. I concentrated for a moment, said a quick prayer to God, gazed at some distant point, and cast the spell. Suddenly I felt a rush of power from my feet, a coalessing of forces from the ground and from my inner core. I threw my arms up and out and from my finger tips came a very large bubble of pulsing maroon light that completely surrounded me. The light quickly faded, but I was left with a sensation of covering, a bit like a very fine gauze all over my body. I was delighted! It worked! It was easy, only a few seconds of concentration and power were required, and instinctively I knew I had a much deeper resevoir to pull from. <br><br>I soon caught site of Aron, quite a handsome figure in all his armour. In the interest of study, I tried to cast the shield spell on him, but, alas, it was for self protection only. Thank God it did not misfire or cause him to become angry or injured! In my excitement, I had not been thinking clearly and just fired blindly. He seemed to be laughing about something when I at last introduced myself and handed him the note. I was sure it was my ignorance. He thanked me for the service, with some coppers, but I was too overwelmed by the site of several nere' do wells running up with guards chasing them to pay any attention to the coinage. They looked to be coming straight at us! <br><br>Gaurdian Aron shouted something at them and turned to me and said "Have at them Nolarita! You have a spell of injury, USE it!" I concentrated on several of the attackers quickly and flung out the other spell I seemed to know.....<br>&nbsp;<br>Nolarita Aurelius, <br>of DAoC, EQ, UO, and finest of all..Legends of Kesmai </td></tr>
