<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100291482827189></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100291482827189><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=10704&mid=100291482827189>DAY ONE TWIGHLIGHT</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=10704&mid=100291482827189#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=10704><span id=Scholar>The One and Only JanaLaser</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>22 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 12th 3:27 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>He says he has a task for me, to get me used to my surroundings and a bit more familiar with the forrest we are in. He wants me to take a note to the Gaurdian Aron who can be found near the Riverbank on the only road in the area. With something akin to gratitude, I take the note and thank him. It helps me to have a task, to focus on something other then my anxiety and ignorance. <br><br>I spent a few minutes walking around the Lethantis Association to make sure I knew where I could find the Mistress again and also to note who else may be there for guidance. I was pleasantly surprised to find a clothing merchant very near, as I knew that I would soon need more protection from the elements and any creatures I might hunt. There were also armed guards, a rather comforting site.<br><br>I spoke to the merchant about prices and how to come by some quick copper to purchase from him, but he was not very informative and really quite busy. I noted the presence of many types of people, and some of the gear they had on, to try to get a feel for what I should acquire. I gave my self time to try and remember the basics of life and movement, much came back quickly to me. My confidence was growing. It was time to journey out from this safe place.....<br>&nbsp;<br>Nolarita Aurelius, <br>of DAoC, EQ, UO, and finest of all..Legends of Kesmai </td></tr>
