<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10028404433134></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10028404433134><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=10704&mid=10028404433134>DAY ONE AM Continued</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=10704&mid=10028404433134#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=10704><span id=Scholar>The One and Only JanaLaser</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>22 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 11th 6:47 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The womans name is Mistress Trethia. Not knowing what else to do, I speak to her. She seems to know that I am confused. She bids me welcome and tells me of the the dark times at hand and the need for defenders of this place. I now know I am in Albion and that Camelot is the name of the main keep. I know something of this, but, only bits and pieces make their way through the cloud that surrounds my mind. A king named Arthur, a Queen ~ Guinevere and something about a table. AH, that brings a sting of pain to my head. A table....a Round Table and Knights, but it is gone again. <br><br>The Mistress tells me other things as I stand there. She tells me of my magical abilities, what spells to use and why a sturdy tree branch has appeared in my hand. She tells me of guilds and arts and pathways. She tells me I have a magical torch to light my footsteps and how to call it to me when needed. I am bewildered by it all and simply stand there and take in what she has to say. People continue to come and go around me, no one noticing me or my dress or my astonishment. The people, in fact, seem very like myself, unsure and overwelmed. <br><br>The day is passing into twilight when Mistress Trethia takes pity on me and says that I may ask her questions.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; "What do you know of me Mistress? How did I come to be here? Why am I in pain? Who is it that I am longing for? Am I dead?" I asked as quickly and as quietly as I could.<br>   She gazed at me deeply with something akin to sorrow on her face, but her voice was light when she said "I know that you are from another time and place, and that many others have come here like you. You are confused now, but time will tell you all you need to know about from where and whence you came. I am not permitted to tell you. All that I can tell you is that you must now make your way in this world. <br><br>It is your choice how you are to go about that, but I know that based on your race, Avalonian, you are inherently good at magic. I know what spells you have now and what will be available to you, based on which path you choose. I can tell you of whom to seek and when to seek them, but that is all. <br><br>As for being dead...do you feel dead? Does this resemble your idea of an afterlife? Do people struggle, hunt, kill, steal, anger, and covet in the next world? Because, I can assure you, they do those things here. You must be on your guard, you must study and grow, you must live to fight another day. You will be needed in the Battles ahead."<br><br>With that she told me that it was time for me to speak to Clorustos, the man standing next to her and then to be on my way, to hunt, to study, to meet new people and find new places. " A blessing upon you Nolarita of the Avalonians ~ may the Ghods keep you and protect and guide you and may you solve the great mystery in which you now find yourself. Come to me again when you have had some time to work on the things we have discussed." She turned to someone else then. I turned to Clorustos with my heart pounding and my knees weak and introduced myself......<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Nolarita Aurelius, <br>of DAoC, EQ, UO, and finest of all..Legends of Kesmai </td></tr>
